-- IATA Gives 90 Days to Air Zimbabwe for Safety Check, Herald Says
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-06-23T07:35:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-23/iata-gives-90-days-to-air-zimbabwe-for-safety-check-herald-says.html
Air Zimbabwe (Pvt) Ltd. has been
given 90 days to conduct a safety audit or face suspension from
foreign airports by the  International Air Transport Association ,
state-controlled Herald reported, citing Innocent Mavhunga, the
airline’s chief executive officer.  The state-owned carrier didn’t conduct its six-monthly
safety audit, which is a condition for IATA membership, the
Harare-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  